<section xml:id="sec-visualising-multidimensional-data">
  <title>Visualising Multidimensional Data</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This section explores techniques for visualising data with multiple variables, helping to reveal patterns and relationships.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Learn techniques for visualising multiple variables</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Understand how to choose appropriate visualisation methods</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Create effective multidimensional visualisations</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-scatter-plots-and-beyond">
    <title>Scatter Plots and Beyond</title>
    <p>
      Scatter plots are fundamental for showing relationships between two variables. Extensions include adding colour, size, and faceting to represent additional dimensions.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-advanced-visualisation">
    <title>Advanced Visualisation Techniques</title>
    <p>
      More advanced techniques include parallel coordinates, heatmaps, and small multiples, which can reveal complex patterns in high-dimensional data.
    </p>
  </subsection>

</section>
